            ">GOP betrays Liz Cheney</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-21-1.jpg" alt="GOP betrays Liz Cheney" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">A <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-21-dec-2024-1" target="_blank">new report</a> accuses GOP Rep. Liz Cheney of unethical behavior while she served on the Jan. 6 committee. It claims she influenced Cassidy Hutchinson's testimony and ignored legal advice. Cheney <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-21-dec-2024-2" target="_blank">denies these accusations</a> and says they are politically motivated lies undermining the committee's findings. Former President Trump supports the allegations and suggests that Cheney broke federal laws. This report is part of ongoing efforts by House Republicans to challenge the Jan. 6 committee's legitimacy, which increases division overviews on the Capitol attack.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The Biden Administration is quietly <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-21-dec-2024-3" target="_blank">considering pardoning her</a> and other political opponents of Trump who he has threatened, such as Adam Schiff and Nancy Pelosi. Senator Bernie Sanders advocates for these pardons as necessary safeguards to protect members of Congress and other figures who could face retaliatory legal actions under a Trump administration.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

