          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Luigi Mangione faces federal charges</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Luigi Mangione, accused of killing UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson, faces both <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-21-dec-2024-4" target="_blank">state and federal charges</a>, including murder as an act of terrorism and firearm-related crimes. The federal charges could carry the death penalty, while the state charges could carry a life imprisonment sentence. Federal prosecutors say that Luigi Mangione meticulously planned the attack on UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson. The primary evidence is the notebook discovered, which was full of handwritten pages expressing his anger and hostility towards the health insurance industry. His lawyers find it unfair that he faces both state and federal charges and was overcharged.  Meanwhile, Mangione had a sea of supporters outside the courtroom giving their support.</p>
        </mj-text>
