              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Under surveillance </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">France's highest court upheld former President Nicolas Sarkozy's <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-21-dec-2024-5" target="_blank">2021 corruption conviction</a>, requiring him to serve a one-year sentence under electronic monitoring. In office from 2007 to 2012, Sarkozy was found guilty of influence-peddling and violating professional secrecy for trying to bribe a judge in 2014 for insider legal information. Denouncing the ruling as a "profound injustice," Sarkozy plans to appeal to the European Court of Human Rights, but this won't delay enforcement. This landmark case makes Sarkozy the second French post-war president convicted of corruption, the other being Jacques Chirac's 2011 sentence.</p>
        </mj-text>
