        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The Polish government will release <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-21-dec-2024-6" target="_blank">1,000 tonnes of butter</a> from its reserves to help lower rising butter prices. The Governmental Strategic Reserves Agency will sell the butter for at least $7 per kilogram. They aim to stabilize the market due to a global milk shortage affecting Poland. According to a recent poll, more than half of Poles blame the government for this rise in butter prices. The presidential candidate Rafal Trzaskowski accused Poland’s central bank of mismanaging inflation and offered to send the governor some butter as proof.</p>
